1
00:00:00,075 --> 00:00:06,838
Constructors in JavaScript classes are special methods used to initialize newly created objects of that class

2
00:00:07,213 --> 00:00:09,250
While creating a new instance of a class

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:14,550
the constructor method is invoked automatically to set up the initial state of the object

4
00:00:14,938 --> 00:00:17,712
This includes setting any default values

5
00:00:17,925 --> 00:00:19,087
binding functions

6
00:00:19,462 --> 00:00:22,712
or performing other startup processes specific to that object

7
00:00:23,087 --> 00:00:29,688
Utilizing constructors effectively allows developers to craft robust and flexible object setups

